(1622, 10214, '愛 AI', '六翼天使〞代表著台灣與全中國人的驕傲，因為從來沒有一支來自中、港、澳的華人樂團能獲得授權，並同時打入日、俄、美洲及歐洲音樂市場，如今〝六翼天使〞做到了！且其國際領土仍持續擴張當中！\r\n\r\n本專輯「愛 AI」是〝六翼天使〞繼前作「平等精靈」後之第三力作，以〝愛〞為寫作出發點的最新概念性專輯，在陣容與音樂風格上皆有些許變動，首先是吉他手黃志華 (Lucas，前Y2K團員) 加入，其精湛的演奏功力相信聽過Y2K創作與表演的樂迷必不陌生。在音樂內容方面則有更為精緻細膩的編曲表現，如加入空心吉他演奏以詮釋情感意境，而節奏快慢與變拍之間的編排則頗有前衛金屬風格 (progressive metal) 的味道，至於主唱Pay的歌唱技巧與音色有更為完美洗煉的表現，這都要歸功她在六翼天使三年來的磨練及德國進修聲樂的成果。整體而言，這是一張兼具樂器技術展現與情感意境表達的概念大作，堪稱〝六翼天使〞之另一傑作！\r\n\r\n為了符合國際化與全球發行，本專輯的封面與內頁交由瑞典知名藝術大師Mattias Noren設計 (Arena, Lost Horizon, Evergrey) 操刀，而為了達到音樂與錄音品質的最佳保證，〝六翼天使〞再次不惜成本飛往芬蘭的FINNVOX STUDIOS進行混音與母帶後製, 在名錄音師Mikko Karmila （Nightwish, Edguy, Stratovarius, Avantasia) 及 Mika Jussila 的精心掌控下，為本作的製作水準寫下絕對保證！', '2004-04-01 00:00:00', 0, 1, 9, '', '', 0, '', 1, 0, '2009-02-15 03:01:46', '2015-02-16 15:47:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1623, 10287, '2002 Live in Anping', '樂手介紹\r\n\r\n*孫和平Axel\r\n吉他 口琴 主唱 詞曲創作\r\n從德國來的外國女婿，已居住台南多年，孩子都在台南長大。音樂是生活中的一部分，因此音樂靈感皆由生活中擷取。現為五月音樂季主辦人，每年五月固定在台南秋茂園舉辦音樂活動。現在再南台之音做DJ主持：主持時間~禮拜一10:00~12:00 禮拜五10:00~12:00，也是樂器行擔任老師，同時從事英文教學。\r\n\r\n\r\n*張保民(阿保)\r\n貝斯 合音\r\n在音樂的造地上教學與演奏的經驗多年,目前為Pub演出的職業樂手，在學友、傑克森……多家樂器公司專任貝斯老師。\r\n\r\n\r\n*李銘根(西部男爵)\r\n鼓手\r\n年輕有為的鼓手，鼓技精義，曾獲得希朵夫音樂比賽第一名。現為爵士鼓專任老師，也是在Pub演出的職業樂手。\r\n', '2002-02-01 00:00:00', 0, 1, 1, '', '', 0, '', 0, 0, '2009-02-15 13:58:20', '2015-02-16 15:47:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1624, 10288, '黑手參', '黑手那卡西第三張專輯！', '2009-02-16 00:00:00', 0, 1, 7, '黑手那卡西工人樂隊', '黑手那卡西工人樂隊', 0, '', 1, 0, '2009-02-16 15:56:09', '2015-02-16 15:47:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1625, 10214, '不死魂', '台灣搖滾史上最璀璨的不朽震撼\r\n        全台搖滾樂迷一致期盼仰望的終極名盤\r\n \r\n\r\n    你是否曾同時聽到天使的呼喚，以及惡魔的咆哮? 此時的你是否已步入夢境，需要特殊的聲音來解除迷惘? 這是一種新的體驗，也是二十一世紀金屬樂的新潮流，而這個趨勢已經在我們所居住的土地上發酵，他是「六翼天使」。\r\n    「六翼天使」擁有引以為傲的古典女詩人小佩做為前導，她的優美音質如天使般聖潔，當她的歌聲與歐洲主流金屬樂相結合，其相互激盪所產生的能量象徵著天使與惡魔，善與惡，以及剛與柔的對立關係，這正是「六翼天使」的音樂訴求。\r\n    為了表現出歐陸金屬特殊的音樂線條，「六翼天使」特別遠赴重洋，到芬蘭最著名的Finnvox錄音室完成母帶後製工作，其展現出的音場效果與層次分明的樂器演奏，皆達到世界一流之水準，再加上「六翼天使」傲人的高度技術及流暢的旋律走向，都足以讓專輯「不死魂」成為台灣金屬/搖滾界的精神標竿。\r\n\r\n', '2001-02-01 00:00:00', 0, 1, 9, '', '', 0, '', 1, 0, '2009-02-17 12:26:06', '2015-02-16 15:47:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1626, 10214, '平等精靈', '在2001年的第一張專輯－【不死魂】裡，六翼天使以女歌劇唱的唱腔搭配些許黑腔對唱，結合技巧派power metal的樂風，在國內引起一陣旋風。老實說，每次在聽第一張專輯－【不死魂】時，總會有一種感覺，好像女主唱和整個音樂一直是搭不起來的，而吉他也是在求快與求技巧，在旋律優美的雕琢，並不受我的喜歡。不過，經過一年的等待，六翼天使終於發行第二張專輯－【平等精靈】。\r\n\r\n首先談談，在這張長達72分鐘的專輯裡，整體的詞曲創作仍是由吉他手許世晃一手包辦，不過，滿令人高興的是六翼天使開始創作一些大型長達九分鐘的曲子，而這些曲子在起承轉合上，作的都滿漂亮的。就整張專輯來說，明顯可以聽到女主唱的部份加重許多，而相較起來黑腔變比較少了，再來，不管在流暢度或是優美度來說，【平等精靈】都比【不死魂】要好上許多，另外，在本張有較多鍵盤／?鋼琴／?提琴等樂音的加入，我想可以更豐富整張專輯的美感與填補雙吉他中的空缺點。其中有幾曲，我個人覺得不錯的，像「沈」／?「最終回憶」／?「平等精靈」／?「終曲」，另外，慢版創作的「驪歌」，不管在優美度與旋律性來說，滿令人欣賞的。\r\n\r\n有人說這張專輯是因為到了芬蘭後製，才變得比較好些，不過，就六翼天使本身來說，可以看得出在編曲與演奏上，花了滿多心思，芬蘭的後製只是更表達他們想要的東西而已。Anyway，我想【平等精靈】應該會比上張【不死魂】，受到更多人喜歡吧。', '2002-02-01 00:00:00', 0, 1, 9, '', '', 0, '', 1, 0, '2009-02-17 12:29:44', '2015-02-16 15:47:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1630, 10369, '龍舌蘭日出 Tequila', '關於Brand New Sin的故事可要回溯到2002年，該團透過Now Or Never Records發行的首張同名專輯「Brand New Sin」，便展現了Brand New Sin(以下簡稱B.N.S.)天生優異的資質、熟捻的技巧以及對於音樂的熱情與硬漢般的態度，綜合成為一股無可否認的生猛搖滾本質，並將B.N.S.推向搖滾樂界的明日之星!! 主唱Joe Altier顆粒明顯的硬漢嗓音搭上紮實的搖滾節奏，令人震驚的出色雙吉他獨奏，遵循著南方藍調搖滾的路線!! 2003年的demo，馬上就被Century Media Records鎖定，於該旗下發行的作品「Recipe For Disaster」，B.N.S.瞬間成為聚焦之的，受到Billboard與Entertainment Weekly大力讚揚，成為Guitar One與Guitar World上不可忽視之樂團，近期更為WWE摔角巨星Big Show製作出場主題曲"Crank It Up"!! 為其硬漢形象大力背書!! \r\n   B.N.S.集Motorhead、Guns N'' Roses、Pantera、Metallica各家精華，灑上Lynyrd Skynyrd的南方憂鬱調味，"永不妥協也不受時光腐蝕的搖滾原力"，Joe Altier說出了B.N.S.的音樂本質!! 最新作品「Tequila」又再次呈現出B.N.S.出色的搖滾原力，與Black Label Society如出一徹的硬漢作風"Did Me Wrong"、"Spare the Agony"與"Motormeth"，南方搖滾的大無謂態度"See the Sun"，Peter Steele(Type O Negative)友情助拳的"Reaper Man"，翻唱英倫經典老團The Animals招牌名曲"House of the Rising Sun"，在借酒消愁的惆悵之餘卻又有著永不妥協的硬漢精神啊!!\r\n    \r\n\r\n   BRAND NEW SIN have returned with a voracious hard rock assault laden with soaring, captivating melodies and crushing anthems that are sure to get anyone''s blood flowing and fists pumping. This highly anticipated new offering, Tequila, features an abundance of stellar guitar work from Kenny Dunham and Kris Wiechmann, who stepped up greatly to further establish themselves as one of rock''s premiere tandems. The Syracuse-based quintet have greatly evolved over the past few years, honing their musicianship to become one of the most acclaimed pure American rock acts around today. \r\n\r\nBRAND NEW SIN first burst upon the scene in 2002 with their groundbreaking self-titled Now Or Never Records debut album. The stunning debut offering was produced by local knobsman Pete Walker at Village Recorders in Liverpool, New York and was one of those rare rock records erected through sheer talent, skill, passion and an iron clad work ethic. It boasted an undeniable raw fury that quickly had critics hailing the band as the next big thing in rock. \r\n\r\nThe group went on to earn a devoted legion of fans through relentless touring with a wide array of artists, from Black Label Society and Slayer to Breaking Benjamin and Saliva. It''s the stunning blend of frontman Joe Altier''s captivating roar and melodic overtones mixed with the band''s gritty, rock-solid rhythm section, stunning dual guitar solos and pummeling hooks that helped this group standout from the pack and appeal to a diverse audience. "Brand New Sin is unyielding rock n'' roll power and timelessness," says Altier, "You can pick our record up 20 years from now and it will still feel as fresh and relevant as it does today." Indeed, BRAND NEW SIN forged a path to ultimately join the ranks of classic bands like AC/DC.\r\n\r\nIn 2003, BRAND NEW SIN added new drummer Kevin Dean to the fold, while longtime guitarists Kenny Dunham, Kris Wiechmann and bassist Chuck Kahl stepped up their involvement. The band ultimately grew tighter and their newfound energy was put into their songwriting for the greater half of 2004, as the band hooked back up with Walker to record their eagerly awaited sophomore offering. The early demos quickly caught the attention of Century Media Records, who immediately signed the band to a worldwide deal. \r\n\r\nThe group stormed back with the stunning Recipe For Disaster album in 2005, which immediately received critical praise from Billboard and Entertainment Weekly, while Guitar One and Guitar World both hailed them as a band to keep an eye on. Recipe For Disaster saw the group begin to find their definitive sound incorporating a variety of metal and hard rock influences ranging from Motorhead and Guns N'' Roses to Pantera and Metallica, while traces of Lynyrd Skynyrd remain evident, lending them the sort of bluesy, swampy edge they are best known for. \r\n\r\nThey proceeded to tour relentlessly with such genre titans as Black Label Society, C.O.C. and Motorhead, further solidifying their diehard fanbase as Fuse and MTV2 embraced the epic track ''Black and Blue.'' They also recently recorded a new version of the entrance theme music for Big Show, the 7-foot, 500-pound ECW wrestler. The theme, "Crank It Up," was first heard on the compilation CD WWE: Wreckless Intent, which debuted at #8 on the Billboard charts. \r\n\r\nBRAND NEW SIN entered Method of Groove studios in Brooklyn with producer Joey Z (Life of Agony, Stereomud) in April of 2006 to begin tracking Tequila and emerged with an album that is sure to stand the test of time. The disc, mastered by the acclaimed George Marino (Metallica, AC/DC, Guns N'' Roses) at Sterling Sound, also features a guest vocal appearance by Peter Steele (Type O Negative) on ''Reaper Man'' and is the perfect representation of what this group is ultimately capable of creating. \r\n\r\nBRAND NEW SIN is the definition of authentic, meat-and-potatoes classic hard rock chased with hints of down home, southern style blues and an undeniable raw fury that refuses to be denied. \r\n', '2006-10-03 00:00:00', 0, 1, 9, '', '', 0, '', 1, 0, '2009-02-17 13:15:22', '2015-02-16 15:47:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1631, 10371, 'The Unspoken King', '加拿大，一直以來給人慵懶愜意、民風樸實的印象，實在很難令人想像可以誕生出如此兇殘的死亡金屬樂團；成軍於1988年，創團初期以Necrosis之名闖蕩魁北克地下搖滾樂壇，其敲打著極端Death Metal音符讓樂團名聲迅速在當地音樂圈中蔓延開；由於對樂手技巧要求甚高，成員變動非常頻繁，最後在瘋狂主唱Lord Worm、鼓手Flo Mounier和吉他手Alex Auburn三位軸心人物先後加入之下，總算替樂團找到明確的創作方向。\r\n\r\n93年自製發表Demo並正式改名為Cryptopsy，隔年隨即加盟獨立廠牌發表首張正式專輯「Blasphemy Made Flesh」，可惜並未引起迴響，直到96年關鍵性的一擊「None So Vile」才讓Cryptopsy真正嚐到成功的滋味；每首歌編曲縝密、複雜又具有深度，就像是一幅結合殘暴與柔美的藝術品；尤其Flo那屌到不像話的超絕鼓技實在令人張目結舌，「None So Vile」理所當然成為樂迷爭相收藏的死亡金屬極經典，也為Cryptopsy贏得一只國際名廠Century Media的合約；就在樂團蓄勢待發，準備大舉進攻國際舞台之同時，Lord Worm表示要離開樂團從事教育工作，主唱部份則改由嗓音偏向Hardcore味道的Mike DiSalvo入替；接下來陸續發表加入旋律色彩以及前衛樂句的「Whisper Supremacy」、「And Then You''ll Beg」，可看出Cryptopsy不斷進步之企圖心，與相近性質的同輩樂團比較之下特顯優異！\r\n\r\n經過Lord Worm短暫回巢之作「Once Was Not」三年後，Cryptopsy首度增添由正妹Maggie Durand所擔任的鍵盤手位置，更網羅前Melodic Death/Metalcore樂團3 Mile Scream的Matt McGachy擔任主唱，推出第六張由團員合力製作的全新專輯「The Unspoken King」，封面散發出中古世紀邪惡帝國之氣息。Matt加入所引起的化學變化讓"Worship Your Demons"、"The Headsmen"呈現Deathcore之厚重力道，證明樂團的全新出發；充滿爵士變拍橋段"Silence The Tyrants"讓樂手實力完全發揮，熟練的技巧搭配絕非泛泛之輩可以比擬；千萬別被"Bemoan The Martyr"、"The Plagued"開頭Matt的順耳清腔給騙到了，隨後馬上以低沉豬吠咆哮將人抓回至混亂漩渦；Alex Auburn刀光劍影的吉他Solo在"Resurgence Of An Empire"中大肆宰殺，沒人能倖免；"Anoint The Dead"重擊程度讓人陷入抓狂情緒；最後，"(Exit) The Few"從開場Matt陰沉的呢喃緩緩鋪陳到最後憤慨思緒被牽動導致型成雜亂無章的群體暴亂，但隨著時間歸零，一且也將化為荒無；留下的，只有這一棟毫無生氣，陰森詭譎的死亡堡壘….', '2008-06-24 00:00:00', 0, 1, 9, '', '', 0, '', 1, 0, '2009-02-17 14:33:01', '2015-02-16 15:47:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1632, 10372, 'Eidolon', '成軍於1994年的Melodic Black Metal亡靈軍團Dark Fortress，來自以旋律/速度而盛名的金屬王朝–"德國"；但他們豪不理會主流市場之運作，以陰森氣氛營造出一首首冰冷詭譎的邪惡之作，建立起一掛極端死忠信徒，登上Summer Breeze Open Air和Kaltenbach Open Air等重金屬音樂祭典；更受到大廠欽點招攬，將Dark Fortress送上國際舞台，打造出德意志黑金屬指標。\r\n\r\n由主腦Asvargyr為首的Dark Fortress，96/97年分別自製Demo、Split開始在地下黑金屬樂壇間廣為流傳；隨即加入獨立廠牌Red Stream，發表「Tales from Eternal Dusk」以及「Profane Genocidal Creations」兩張作品，對於Dark Fortress那毫無人性的血腥作風，無疑是給了養慣順耳旋律的德國民眾一記當頭棒喝！04年轉入Black Attakk旗下推出封面由知名異類藝術家Travis Smith操刀的「Stab Wounds」；雖團員更動頻繁，主要還是以Asvargyr以及01年入團的V. Santura為創作中心。 \r\n\r\n現在，Dark Fortress帶來入主Century Media的第二作、也是樂團第五張的正式專輯「Eidolon」重返人間，繼續襲擊毫無防備的愚蠢人類。知名金屬雜誌Metal hammer奉上７/10高度評鑑！開場的"The Silver Gate"引領出毛骨悚然之低靡氣壓，隨即爆出高速雙踏、猛烈吉他刷扣，新主唱Morean齜牙列嘴的嘶吼把人推進無窮無盡的黑暗深淵中；"Cohorror"就像出地獄、手持鞭莿的惡魔不斷瘋狂往人們身上抽打；"Baphomet"有著Black/Doom名團Celtic Frost的主唱Tom Gabriel Fischer參與屠殺；"Analepsy"摧毀一切事物的既定認知合理性；明朗鼓點，扭曲吉他導入的"Edge of Night"為專輯內唯一旋律較明朗的歌曲，你以為痛楚結束了嗎？不，"No Longer Human"將再度燃燒你的皮膚，吞食你的靈魂… \r\n\r\n經過「Eidolon」內九層無間煉獄的強烈摧殘，你覺得你還能剩下什麼？\r\n\r\nLineup changes are very much the norm in black metal; a black metal band that can go ten or more years without any lineup changes is the exception instead of the rule -- and like so many other European black metal outfits, Dark Fortress have had their share of personnel changes since their formation in Germany in 1994. Dark Fortress experienced some major upheaval and turmoil in 2007, when their original lead singer, Matthias Jell (aka Azathoth), took off after 13 years with the band and was replaced by Morean (founder of the band Noneuclid). But Dark Fortress bounce back nicely on their first post-Azathoth album, Eidolon. This 2008 release is a concept album based on the Greek idea of an astral double, which is similar to the German concept of a doppelgänger. Some concept albums work well as a whole but lose something if you only hear selected or individual songs; however, that isn''t a problem at all on Eidolon. Every song on this 52-minute CD can stand on its own regardless of whether or not one hears the other tracks; that is as true of "The Unflesh," "Catacrusis," and "Cohorror" as it is of "Edge of Night" (which has nothing whatsoever to do with the American film noir/crime thriller-themed daytime soap opera that ran from 1956-1984 -- first on CBS, then on ABC -- although the song''s title will bring smiles to the faces of those who are old enough to remember that program). Brutally heavy yet darkly atmospheric and fairly melodic, Eidolon achieves a stylistic middle ground that fans of more mainstream metal might find to be more accessible than Gorgoroth or Marduk but less accessible than Dimmu Borgir. Morean sticks to sinister-sounding rasp vocals and never ventures into clean vocals, but he doesn''t render the lyrics indecipherable -- and he proves to be a major asset for Dark Fortress throughout the excellent Eidolon.\r\n', '2008-03-11 00:00:00', 0, 1, 9, '', '', 0, '', 1, 0, '2009-02-17 14:44:33', '2015-02-16 15:47:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1633, 10372, 'Séance', '來自金屬王朝德意志，亡靈軍團Dark Fortress挾以陰森氛圍塑造出一首首冰冷詭譎的邪惡之作，毫無畏懼主流市場沉重壓力且決不向商業靠攏的曲式理念，不但建立起一票死忠信徒，成為當代黑金屬全新指標，並贏得金屬名廠欽點邀約，把黑暗的絕望思想大舉推向人間！\r\n\r\n由Asvargr(吉他)、Azathoth(主唱)與Njord(貝斯)三人在1994年時共同打造的死亡堡壘Dark Fortress憑藉撒旦的兇殘本質吸引到一票死忠樂迷，自製Demo和Split讓樂團名聲迅速在地下黑金屬圈中蔓延開。在加入Charon(鼓)、Crom(吉他)與Thamuz(鍵盤)等團員後的Dark Fortress於獨立廠牌Red Stream陸續發表「Tales from Eternal Dusk(2001)」、「Profane Genocidal Creations(2003)」兩張作品，不但得到雜誌樂評的讚譽，對於極端金屬信徒來說更是愛不釋手！2004年樂團轉入Black Attakk旗下，請來Travis Smith(Trivium)負責第三張專輯「Stab Wounds」的封面及內頁藝術設計，將其獨特黑闇氣勢透過視覺與聽覺完美呈現。\r\n\r\n雖然成軍10多年間團員更動速度頗為頻繁，卻無損Dark Fortress的實力，依舊保有超高度毀滅能量；2006年除元老Asvargr(吉他)與Azathoth(主唱)外，換上V. Santura(吉他)、Draug(貝斯)、Paymon(鍵盤)以及Seraph(鼓)的全新陣容推出加盟Century Media第四張專輯「Séance」。藉由充滿強烈不安感觸"Ghastly Indoctrination"揭開序幕，Azathoth那猶如地獄魔鬼般嗓音解構在冰冷的低聲囈語及哀嚎下；"CataWomb"引出令人毛骨悚然燬暗氣味直衝"To Harvest the Artefacts of Mockery"，喚醒體內沉睡許久的殺戮本性；冷血無情的"Poltergeist"將踐踏一切神聖事物；"Incide"淒厲慘叫劃破黑夜寧靜，人類正遭受痛苦萬分的嗜血殘虐，並墮入到"Insomnia"永不超生的閻闇空間。', '2006-01-30 00:00:00', 0, 1, 9, '', '', 0, '', 1, 0, '2009-02-17 15:08:09', '2015-02-16 15:47:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1634, 10373, 'Character', '俗稱哥登堡之聲的NWOSDM(New Wave Of Swedish Death Metal)，並以Dark Tranquility、In Flames、At The Gates為首在90年代中葉叱吒風雲，融合北歐民族的哀愁情懷以及民謠元素，擷取死亡金屬之暴力性格創造出音樂個性強烈的金屬支流，力與美的完美共存，可說是金屬樂界的重要創舉。而1995年該團第二張作品即經典專輯「The Gallery」與At The Gates的「Slaughter Of The Soul」、In Flames的「The Jester Race」的優異表現，更將這一波哥登堡之聲的熱潮推升至更高的境界。\r\n    自「Projector」之後逐漸改變原本較為狂暴航向的Dark Tranquility(以下簡稱D.T.)，往人性更深層的黑暗、哀愁、不安、焦慮、憤怒前進，頗有經典專輯「The Gallery」開頭曲” Punish My Heaven”之氣勢的” The New Build”，長期壓抑的情緒馬上爆發，人類的盲目自大招致心靈上的自我毀滅，power chord依舊姿意狂放的”Through Smudged Lenses”，標準D.T.後期作風的”Out of Nothing”，以及意識矛盾的” Am I 1?”，意有所指的說明了近年來複製人所將會為人類社會帶來的嚴重議題。\r\n    當同鄉In Flames開始為了打入美國市場，逐漸轉型為帶有Nu-Metal風格之時，D.T.依然鎮守哥登堡之聲的最後一道防線，時間可以證明，「Character」也可以證明誰才是真正的王道!!\r\n\r\nHaving taken longer than most of Gothenburg, Sweden''s death metal giants to reveal their greatness, Dark Tranquility have now arguably become that ever-popular subgenre''s most enduring torch-bearers -- the living embodiment of melodic death metal midway through the ''00s. And, in keeping with that station, 2005''s Character marks the third installment of what most agree has been the band''s most consistent career-phase; one which finds them, like other genre standard-bearers before them (Iron Maiden, AC/DC, Black Sabbath, anyone?), reveling in their mastery of a formula they know so well it inevitably begs the question: have they become too comfortable in their niche? Are they stagnating? Well, there''s a distinct difference between beating a dead horse and riding it to victory every time, and Character sure feels like the latter, as song after memorable song storms by all limbs a-flailing and death-shrieks a-shrieking, their riffs and harmonies stacked as densely as only Dark Tranquility can stack them. If anything, this outing follows a slightly more straightforward and aggressive tact than its two acclaimed predecessors, using well-placed synthesizer breaks and melodies to heighten, not suffocate, the ferocious onslaught driving the nearly black metal barrage of "The New Build," the overpowering fury of "Lost to Apathy," and the brilliantly schizophrenic "Dry Run." In fact, only the rather electronics-heavy "The Endless Feed" and the especially emotive quasi-ballad "My Negation" ever manage to distract us from the dominant maelstroms raging here. Admittedly, there''s probably no single perfect offering on Character on par with Haven''s "Not Built to Last" or Damage Done''s "Cathode Ray Sunshine," but there''s also no real weak links to speak of, either -- perhaps the less-than-marvelous, "Mind Matters" and "Am I 1?" But, for all intents and purposes, what we have here is quite simply state-of-the-art melodic death metal.\r\n', '2005-01-25 00:00:00', 0, 1, 9, '', '', 0, '', 1, 0, '2009-02-17 15:18:42', '2015-02-16 15:47:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1635, 10373, 'Damage Done', 'Dark Tranquillity (以下簡稱D.T.) 的成立正象徵著旋律死亡金屬樂派 (Melodic Death Metal，簡稱M.D.) 的興起，而這段金屬樂史上的中興時刻當溯及至1993年當D.T.發行了首張專輯「Skydancer」之時，其以饒富北歐哀愁情懷之黑、死亡金屬風格，創新並融合出屬於瑞典音樂重鎮Gothenburg的金屬之音，堪稱金屬樂界的一大創舉！\r\n    1995年為New Wave Of Swedish Death Metal最風光的一年，當時有At The Gates的「Slaughter Of The Soul」，In Flames的「The Jester Race」，以及D.T.第二作「The Gallery」的發行，為M.D.樂派奠定了不朽之基，同時也確立了上述樂團三巨頭的地位。D.T.在發行了第三作「The Mind''s I」之後隨即脫離Osmose，並與金屬大廠Century Media簽下合約，發表了「Projector」與「Haven」兩張兼具氣氛營造和金屬破壞力的成熟作品，也為M.D.的深度及廣度再度加分。\r\n    D.T.的第六張專輯 -「Damage Done」在音樂上以幽暗詭譎氣氛引領出北國的哀愁派金屬氣息，在內容方面則藉著科技的發達來突顯人性的不安與憤怒。首曲 "Final Resistance" 以雷霆萬鈞的金屬雷擊展現出忍無可忍的怒氣；而到了 "The Treason Wall" 一曲更將M.D.樂派最要的power melody完全展露。專輯同名曲在曲式快與緩之間遊走，道出了內心的矛盾與衝突。末曲 "Ex Nihilo" 則以抽象的金屬交響演奏形式帶領探索虛無的靈魂空間，您即將準備進入嗎？\r\n\r\nDark Tranquillity is able to find beauty -- as odd as that may sound -- in the extreme elements of death metal. Much more than mere noise artists, this Swedish sextet understands the importance of melody (usually minor key) and texture (occasionally ambient), and their hurtling aggression is imbued with a dark, neo-classical sense of composition, rather than the atonal chromaticism favored by similar (particularly American) acts. Damage Done should please metal fans who appreciate both death metal''s extreme qualities and progressive metal''s musicality, but it may not appeal to purists from either camp.\r\n', '2002-08-20 00:00:00', 0, 1, 9, '', '', 0, '', 1, 0, '2009-02-17 15:20:38', '2015-02-16 15:47:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1636, 10373, 'Fiction', '哥登堡之聲，那種在北地冰霜包負之下的熱能是特別能夠引起熱血澎湃!!\r\n    瑞典旋律死亡金屬先鋒Dark Tranquillity，凱旋般的再次帶來了新專輯「Fiction」，那股灼熱的音樂態度鎔鑄了Dark Tranquillity先前的所有元素，形成一個樂風的積合體，言之有物的憤怒、雕工精細的吉他、激起熱血漣漪的漂亮旋律與純粹的凶暴，並且在融合之時又併出新的火花，可說是對於樂團早年經典「The Gallery」及「The Mind’s I」的現代呼應!! \r\n    "Nothing To No One"哀傷包覆在兇猛的外殼之下，熱血澎湃一觸即發!! "The Lesser Faith"以及主打曲"Focus Shift"成熟穩健的Dark Tranquillity式編曲，回歸老派作風"Blind At Heart"，中期哀怨感厚重之"Inside The Particle Storm"，早期後期元素大融合之"Empty Me"，架構出「Fiction」樂風積合的旋律藍圖。\r\n    製造結合力與美的哥登堡之聲熱血不斷，將近20年的運轉，歷經時間的沖刷，Dark Tranquillity已創造出最適合現代的旋律死亡金屬!!\r\n\r\nIntricacy, musicality, craftsmanship, and nuance are words that, back in 1989, were hardly ever used to describe death metal -- a style so extreme, so ferocious, so intent on annoying parents at any cost that it seemed destined to self-destruct. But Dark Tranquillity and their expansive colleagues in Gothenburg, Sweden, refused to believe that death metal could not be musical, nuanced, and melodic, and that outlook continues to define them on Fiction. This rewarding CD was recorded in 2006 and released in 2007, the year that marked Dark Tranquillity''s 18th anniversary. Perhaps 18 years isn''t all that long compared to the Rolling Stones celebrating their 45th anniversary in 2007; nonetheless, 18 is an impressive number when one recalls all the naysayers who, in the late ''80s, thought death metal would be long gone by the 21st century. But Dark Tranquillity not only survived -- they continued to provide highly consistent discs such as Fiction, which, like many of their previous releases, achieves a healthy, coherent, natural-sounding balance of the melodic and the extreme. Melodic death metal is the album''s orientation, but there are other influences as well, including black metal (lead singer Mikael Stanne''s sinister rasp vocals have a lot of black metal appeal on Fiction), alternative metal, darkwave, and goth. In fact, the darkwave-drenched "Misery''s Crown" (which finds Stanne providing mostly clean vocals) is really more goth metal than death metal; it''s a gem that would not be out of place on a My Dying Bride album -- and for that matter, the Crüxshadows would probably have an easy time covering the song if they toned down its metal aspects. Not that Dark Tranquillity need to tone anything down; Fiction is excellent the way it is, and it''s great to see these Swedes very much on top of their game after many years in the death metal trenches.\r\n', '2007-04-24 00:00:00', 0, 1, 9, '', '', 0, '', 1, 0, '2009-02-17 15:23:00', '2015-02-16 15:47:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(1637, 10373, 'Exposures', '以一張經典作品「The Gallery」、與另外三組同樣來自瑞典的樂團In Flame、At The Gates、Dissection，豪不畏懼90年代龐然掀起的另類音樂效應，聯手將整個旋律死亡金屬推向全世界，達到樂界的至高點，創造出俗稱的哥登堡之聲，他就是Dark Tranquillity。\r\n\r\n原本就是好友的Niklas Sundin(吉他)、Martin Henriksson(貝斯)和Anders Jivarp(鼓)於1991年組成Dark Tranquillity，93年找來Anders Friden擔任主唱發表首張專輯「Skydancer」，雖然沒有造成廣大迴響但也為樂團之後的路打好了基礎；稍後Friden離團加入In Flames改由Mikael Stanne入替，Mikael優異的創作能力帶給了樂團全新契機；果不然，95年「The Gallery」以及97年「The Mind''s I」雙雙替Dark Tranquillity寫下最光輝的一頁，並帶起旋律死金浪潮影響了整個歐洲樂壇，更為樂團爭取到名廠Century Media的一只合約。團員先是在編制上做了小幅更動，原本站貝斯位置的Martin改接掌吉他並加入新血Martin Brandstrom(鍵盤)和Michael Nicklasson(貝斯)，整裝完畢後陸續推出「Projector」與「Haven」這兩張金屬破壞力和氣氛營造兼具的成熟作品，為Melodic Death的深度內涵再度加分。\r\n\r\n繼2002年「Damage Done」得到專業音樂網站AMG四星高度評鑑、大受好評之餘，Dark Tranquillity特別推出雙CD大包裝精選「Exposures - In Retrospect and Denial」獻給長久以來支持他們的死忠信徒！CD1完整蒐集樂團歷年來所有未正式曝光之作品以及B-Side、Demo，讓樂迷們不用在大費周章去二手市場尋找；\r\nCD2則收錄 2002年樂團在波瀾Live Damage演唱會的現場實況錄音，絕佳的效果呈現彌補了無法親身參與盛會而失落的心情。假設你尚未接觸過Dark Tranquillity的音樂，這會是你最好的入門途徑；假設你是Dark Tranquillity的忠實樂迷，那你的CD架上就更不該缺少這張精選特輯！\r\n\r\nInitially overlooked amidst the towering wave of heavy metal talent coming out of Sweden in the early 1990s (the so-called "New Wave of Swedish Death Metal"), Gothenburg natives Dark Tranquillity eventually matured -- along with cross-town rivals In Flames -- into possibly the ultimate expression of melodic death metal. Helping to make that case is 2004''s Exposures: In Retrospect and Denial -- a timely "odds & sods" collection purging the band''s creative closet and unearthing some long lost treasures from their past. Its first seven offerings comprise assorted outtakes and B-sides from the band''s three, increasingly top-notch releases leading up to this set, and although the overly dramatic clean singing first attempted on (and abandoned shortly after) 1998''s Projector remains a botched experiment (see "Misery in Me"), even the rejects from its brilliant "back-to-death-vocals" successors, 2000''s Haven, and 2002''s Damage Done, are about as good as Gothenburg metal gets. Up next, five primeval cuts -- two from 1992 7" A Moonclad Reflection, and three from 1991''s "Trail of Life Decayed" demo -- open a time warp to the group''s very inception. Not surprisingly, more aggressive, excessively busy tracks like "Yesterworld," "Unfurled by Dawn," and "Final Resistance" recall contemporary sounds by the likes of Edge of Sanity and Entombed -- a far cry from Dark Tranquillity''s refined and distinctive aesthetic yet to come. Finally, a bonus DVD containing audio-only of 19 songs featured in the band''s Live Damage DVD (always a sketchy proposition, but better than nothing) supplies yet another treat for die-hard fans, as indeed will this entire package.\r\n', '2004-06-15 00:00:00', 0, 1, 9, '', '', 0, '', 1, 0, '2009-02-17 15:26:11', '2015-02-16 15:47:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
